{
  "texts": [
    "at(i, 1) can be real-valued scalar or integer numbers obtained by a one-hot or multi-hot encoding method.",
    "Thus a record for the learner l i can be formulated as follows:where Fa(L) represents selected attribute feature records for a collection of learners L (with M learners), N at denotes that we choose N at attribute features for the global sam- pling.",
    "Specifically, Fa(L) is generated only from the training dataset, not all the raw data from LMS, through which the problem of predicting the current states with possible future information can be avoided.",
    "(1)Ac(l i) = {ac(i, 1), ac(i, 2),..., ac(i, N aci)}, (2) Fg(L) = {Ac(l 1), Ac(l 2),..., Ac(l M)}, (3) At(l i) = {at(i, 1), at(i, 2),..., at(i, N ati)}, (4) Fa(L) = {At(l 1), At(l 2),..., At(l M)}, Dynamic graph constructionThe subsection details how to use the data from Eq.",
    "( 2) to construct the dynamic temporal graphs as the input for low-high filtering temporal graph networks in APP-TGN."
  ]
